Articles.Content:
@regex

It may be how Squad has been handling these issues, but as you said, it's a shame and unfortunately tends to result in the rampant speculation (I'm guilty of it as well) that we see time and again, especially since 1.0 was announced.

@juanml82

I know that Squad needs to recruit new players, and 1.0 will definitely bring a fair number of them, but a buggy initial release is a great way to get a lot of negative PR and dry up the influx of new customers, especially for a niche game like this (the learning curve is still a bit too vertical, hopefully the new tutorials will help, and career is seriously lacking in meaningful things to do, this game is really just a giant sandbox). Don't underestimate the power of game ratings, especially on Steam. I've passed over many interesting looking games because of poor ratings.

I'm not suggesting Squad should share the details of their financial records, by details I was referring to details on the current state of the game from a development standpoint with an honest assessment of the progress. If financials and/or retail commitments are playing a part in the 1.0 release than Squad should at least acknowledge that, but I understand that details of such things don't need to be disclosed.

